              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/37174093/" class="">Chapter 23: The Coming Revolt of the Guards</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/Aspire/" class=" " title="Jiong">Jiong</a>
              
                <span class="allstar40" title="推荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="37174093">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">It is a history disrespectful of governments and  respectful of people's movements of resistance. That makes it a biased account, one that leans in a certain direction. I am not troubled by that, because the mountain of history books under which we all stand leans so heavily in the other direction --- so tremblingly respectful of states and statesmen and so disrespectful, by inattention, to people...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2016-02-13 16:50</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>It is a history disrespectful of governments and  respectful of people's movements of resistance. That makes it a biased account, one that leans in a certain direction. I am not troubled by that, because the mountain of history books under which we all stand leans so heavily in the other direction --- so tremblingly respectful of states and statesmen and so disrespectful, by inattention, to people's movements --- that we need some counterforce to avoid being crushed into submission.</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>偏见往往是一种独特的视角。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Howard Zinn在书里也说，在没有出版监管的美国其实要了解到这样的美国历史也不容易。
