                  <span class="">Las Casas tells how the Spaniards &quot;grew more conceited every day&quot; and after a while refuse to walk any distance. They &quot;rode the back of Indians if they were in a hurry&quot; or were carried on hammock by Indians running in relays. &quot;In this case they also had Indians carry large leaves to shade them from the sun and others to fan them with goose wings.&quot;

